<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,1782,1915]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Described from 
<collectingCountry box="[333,464,1782,1807]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
and recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[684,729,1783,1806]" name="Iran" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Iran</collectingCountry>
this species has the hind femur narrower than is usual amongst species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1820" box="[268,416,1818,1843]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[268,416,1818,1843]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Platycephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The larva develops in 
<taxonomicName box="[675,909,1818,1843]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[675,909,1818,1843]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Phragmites australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. At my request Dr. Nartshuk kindly dissected a female 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nartshuk" authorityYear="1964" box="[236,314,1855,1878]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Eurina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis box="[236,314,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and found it to be monoovariolate. The male terminalia as figured in the original description and later by 
<bibRefCitation box="[243,500,1890,1915]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref41065" refString="Andersson, H. (1977) Taxonomic and phylogenetic studies on Chloropidae (Diptera) with special reference to Old World genera. In: Entomologica scandinavica. 8 (Supplement). Scandinavian Science Press, Klampenborg, pp. 1 - 200." type="book chapter">Andersson (1977: 128)</bibRefCitation>
are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1907" box="[816,948,1890,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Eurina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scapularum">
<emphasis box="[816,948,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">scapularum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
